  "local_port": 39310,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What should I do to get selected in GSOC 2018?",
  "response": "To get selected for Google Summer of Code (GSoC) 2018, here are some steps you can follow to increase your chances:\n\n1. **Understand GSoC:** Familiarize yourself with the GSoC program, including its objectives, timeline, and requirements. Visit the official GSoC website for up-to-date information.\n\n2. **Choose the Right Organization:** Research and select organizations that match your interests and skills. Look at their projects, community, and mentors. Choose an organization that you feel passionate about.\n\n3. **Start Early:** Many successful candidates begin preparing months in advance. Engage with the community, contribute to the organization\u2019s existing projects, and get to know the mentors.\n\n4. **Contribute to the Organization:** Before applying, contribute to the organization\u2019s repository by fixing bugs or implementing features. This will not only demonstrate your skills but also show your commitment.\n\n5. **Get Involved in the Community:** Participate in mailing lists, forums, or chats. Ask questions, seek feedback, and build relationships with community members.\n\n6. **Select a Project Idea:** Choose a project idea that interests you and aligns with your skill set. If the organization has multiple ideas, you can suggest your own as well, but make sure it adheres to their goals.\n\n7. **Write a Strong Proposal:** Your project proposal should be clear, well-structured, and detailed. Highlight your qualifications, outline the project\u2019s goals, timeline, and deliverables. Mention how you plan to communicate with your mentor and integrate feedback.\n\n8. **Show Your Work:** Include examples of your previous work, such as code samples, projects, or contributions to open-source software. This will demonstrate your skills and experience.\n\n9. **Seek Feedback:** Share your proposal draft with community members or mentors to get feedback. Incorporate their suggestions to make your proposal stronger.\n\n10. **Prepare for the Coding Phase:** Once selected, be ready to commit to the project. Create a timeline for deliverables and keep communication lines open with your mentor.\n\n11. **Be Persistent:** If you aren\u2019t selected, don\u2019t be discouraged. Seek feedback, improve your skills, and try again in future rounds. \n\nRemember, every year the guidelines and requirements may change slightly, so always refer to the official GSoC page for the latest information. Good luck!",
